article.linkText: Hopkins, Lane help Prairie View A&M edge Florida A&M 61-58
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- — Javontae Hopkins and Charles Lane Jr. scored 18 points apiece to help Prairie View A&M hold off Florida A&M 61-58 on Monday night. Hopkins also contributed seven rebounds for the Panthers (10-14, 5-6 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Lane made 7 of 12 shots with two 3-pointers. Brian Myles scored 12. The Rattlers (4-18, 2-9) were led by Shannon Grant with 15 points, six rebounds and two blocks. Jalen Speer added 13 points and six rebounds. Matthew Webster totaled eight points and 16 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
